Picture quality sucks like off the street bootlegs. Sound is in good condition. Torrent is all right for those who really want to see the movie.

OK now, I'm one of those viewers who REALLY dislikes bad quality movies but I have to admit that this movie is 100% worth it. Time as currency? Probably one of the most unique ideas of all the movies I have seen in my time - but onto the quality.

Remember, its not a DVD Rip, don't expect anything solid. If I was to rate this on a scale of 10, 1 being Minecraft and 10 being DVD Rip, it would place somewhere around 6.

If you are on the other hand, used to cams, this is a 8-9/10.

Overall I would give it an average rating of:
V: 7
A: 8 (Some static at certain points but otherwise very good)
M: A must watch, but if you're patient enough to wait for a rip, definitely do that.
